  "version": 2,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-15",
  "title": {
    "en": "The Birth of Isaac"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "God speaks again to Abraham—this time about Sarai.",
      "He gives her a new name and announces a son, Isaac, will be born to her."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "new_name",
        "icon": "badge",
        "label": { "en": "Sarai Becomes Sarah" },
        "lines": [
          "God also said to Abraham,",
          "“As for Sarai your wife,",
          "you are no longer to call her Sarai;",
          "her name will be Sarah.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "son",
        "icon": "family",
        "label": { "en": "A Son Is Named" },
        "lines": [
          "Then God said,",
          "“Yes, but your wife Sarah will bear you a son,",
          "and you will call him Isaac.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "covenant",
        "icon": "handshake",
        "label": { "en": "An Everlasting Covenant" },
        "lines": [
          "“I will establish my covenant with him",
          "as an everlasting covenant",
          "for his descendants after him.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What stands out to you about the way God speaks and makes promises here?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Genesis 17:15–21"]
  }
}
